================================================================================
6. DETAILED FAILURE ANALYSIS
================================================================================

6.1 empty_result (5 failures)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  These tasks exhausted all 4 steps without the LLM producing a final answer.

  task_022  ItemService.save              medium   7,535ms  4 steps
  task_030  InstanceService.getByNamespace medium  6,947ms  4 steps
  task_032  NamespaceController.delete     medium  7,195ms  4 steps
  task_038  NamespaceService.findParentNamespace hard 7,572ms 4 steps
  task_044  ReleaseService.publish         hard    8,615ms  4 steps

  Root Cause: Agent spent all steps searching/reading but never converged
  on a final answer. Likely cause: too many rg hits, agent kept reading
  files trying to disambiguate but ran out of steps.

6.2 wrong_line (5 failures)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Correct file identified, but line number off by more than 3.

  task_023  AppService.findOne             medium  expected=73  predicted=53  delta=20
  task_024  ClusterService.delete          medium  expected=105 predicted=88  delta=17
  task_033  ConfigController.queryConfig   medium  expected=95  predicted=79  delta=16
  task_037  NamespaceService.isChildNamespace hard expected=280 predicted=284 delta=4
  task_043  PermissionController.hasPermission hard expected=93 predicted=76  delta=17

  Root Cause:
  - task_037: Off by only 4 lines (one overload away) -- borderline miss
  - Others: Agent picked a different method in the same class, or miscounted
    lines after reading a partial file range.

6.3 api_error (4 failures)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  LLM API returned an error; no prediction was made.

  task_025  ReleaseService.publish         medium   3,513ms
  task_026  AppService.findAll             medium   2,924ms
  task_045  ItemController.get             hard     7,177ms
  task_050  ReleaseMessageListener.handleMessage edge 1,331ms

  Root Cause: deepseek-v4-flash API intermittent errors (rate limiting,
  timeouts, or transient failures). These are infrastructure issues,
  not agent logic failures. Retrying would likely resolve most.

6.4 wrong_file (2 failures)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Agent identified the wrong file entirely.

  task_027  NamespaceService.deleteNamespace
            Expected: apollo-portal/.../NamespaceService.java
            Predicted: apollo-biz/.../NamespaceService.java

  task_028  ReleaseService.rollback
            Expected: apollo-portal/.../ReleaseService.java
            Predicted: apollo-biz/.../ReleaseService.java

  Root Cause: Both failures involve the same pattern -- the agent found
  a class with the same name in the biz module instead of the portal
  module. The portal module duplicates several service class names
  (NamespaceService, ReleaseService, AppService), and the agent
  defaulted to the first rg hit (alphabetically, biz comes before portal).

================================================================================
7. KEY INSIGHTS
================================================================================

7.1 Grep Agent Strengths
  - Perfect (100%) on class, enum, and interface searches
  - Fast median latency (4.3s) for successful tasks
  - Efficient step usage: most tasks complete in 3 steps
  - Handles inner classes/enums well (AdminServiceAPI.ItemAPI, etc.)

7.2 Grep Agent Weaknesses
  - Method disambiguation is the primary failure mode
  - Cannot distinguish between identically-named classes in different
    modules (biz vs portal)
  - Step limit (4) is tight for ambiguous method searches
  - No module-awareness: treats all rg results equally regardless of
    which module they belong to

7.3 Difficulty Anomaly
  - Hard tasks (50%) outperform medium tasks (33.3%)
  - Explanation: Hard tasks include inner classes/enums (unique names),
    while medium tasks specifically target ambiguous method names across
    modules -- the Grep Agent's weakest capability

7.4 Infrastructure Impact
  - 4 API errors (8%) account for 25% of all failures
  - Excluding API errors: 34/(50-4) = 73.9% effective success rate
  - Excluding API errors + empty_result: agent logic failures = 12/46 = 73.9%

================================================================================
8. CONCLUSION
================================================================================

The Grep Agent achieves 68.0% overall success rate on the Apollo codebase
symbol localization benchmark, with perfect performance on unique-name
symbols (class/enum/interface) but significant challenges on ambiguous
method-name resolution across modules.

Primary bottleneck: the agent lacks module-level awareness when multiple
classes share the same name across different Apollo modules (biz, portal,
adminservice, configservice). This is an inherent limitation of text-based
grep search without structural code understanding.

Secondary bottleneck: API reliability (4 transient errors) accounts for
a disproportionate share of failures.

