================================================================================
Appendix B: Bugs Fixed During Experiment
================================================================================

B1. Windows path normalization in grep_tools.py
    - rg_search returned raw OS paths with backslashes
    - glob_files returned backslash-separated paths
    - rg_search included codebases/apollo/ prefix in file paths
    Fix: Normalize to forward slashes and strip codebase prefix

B2. Markdown artifact in LLM output parsing (grep_agent.py)
    - LLM wrapped paths in markdown: `path`, **path**, etc.
    - _parse_answer used greedy (.+?):(\d+) which captured artifacts
    Fix: Use restrictive regex ([\w\-./]+\.java):(\d+) + strip markdown chars

    Impact: Without B2 fix, only 7/50 (14%) succeeded. With fix: 34/50 (68%).

